\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 The Three Things Your Developer Needs To Know\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 1. Every feature is org-scoped via RLS.
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Never query without the 
\f3\fs26 organization_id
\f0\fs24  filter \'97 Supabase RLS enforces it, but the API routes also manually verify membership. The helper functions 
\f3\fs26 get_my_org_ids()
\f0\fs24  and 
\f3\fs26 has_org_role()
\f0\fs24  are baked into every policy.\

\f1\b 2. The scanner role is a first-class citizen.
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 It's not a watered-down admin. It's a completely separate authenticated session with its own route group 
\f3\fs26 (scanner)/
\f0\fs24  and its own API access scope. A scanner user cannot navigate to 
\f3\fs26 /dashboard
\f0\fs24 , 
\f3\fs26 /settings
\f0\fs24 , or any admin page.\

\f1\b 3. Raw OCR never becomes truth directly.
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 The godmode pipeline exists specifically to prevent bad data entering the system. Extraction 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  arbitration 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  validation 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  human review 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  canonicalization 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  embedding. That ordering is intentional and must be preserved for any new document type or OCR lane added.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 Bottom line on the plan vs reality:
\f0\b0  About 85% of the suggested architecture is live. The scanner system, iPad-first UI, multi-engine pipeline, in-app capture, own-cloud storage, classification at scan time, two capture modes (batch vs evidence), and all the fallbacks are implemented. The remaining 15% is the ABBYY-grade mobile capture SDK, offline queue, and live FAA DRS API integration \'97 all feasible additions on top of the existing foundation.\
